<p><b>Ian Kevin Curtis</b> (15 July 1956&#160;– 18 May 1980) was the vocalist and lyricist, as well as occasional guitarist and keyboardist, of the band <a href="/wiki/Joy_Division" title="Joy Division">Joy Division</a>, which he joined in 1976 after meeting with <a href="/wiki/Bernard_Sumner" title="Bernard Sumner">Bernard Sumner</a> and <a href="/wiki/Peter_Hook" title="Peter Hook">Peter Hook</a> at a <a href="/wiki/Sex_Pistols" title="Sex Pistols">Sex Pistols</a> gig.</p>
<p>Years after his death, critics and fans continue to write and discuss at length Curtis's music, as well as possible motivations and inspirations for his work. News of his <a href="/wiki/Suicide" title="Suicide">suicide</a> in 1980 spurred many rumours, further accelerating interest in his work and troubled life.</p>
